    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You've built your skysteel multi-tool to be extremely compact and convertible, allowing you to transform it into another configuration. When you select this feat, you build a second multi-tool using the engineer's multi-tool rules, starting with 12 TP just like your regular multi-tool. This configuration becomes your invention's second configuration.</p><p>Select a new set of skysteel modifications for this new configuration. You can spend two Interact actions to switch your multi-tool between the two configurations. These actions don't need to be taken consecutively, but if you've provided the first and not the second, the weapon is non-functional as it is stranded between states. Your weapon's Bulk is always the greater Bulk of the two configurations, regardless of which configuration it's in â€” if one weapon is smaller than the other, you still need to keep any weapon parts on hand. Any materia on your multi-tool affect the second weapon configuration, as long as it would normally qualify for them.</p>",
